  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of disguising the origin of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Key legal elements typically include:\n\n1. Legal components:\n- Concealing the source of illegally obtained funds\n- Transforming illegal money into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Conducting financial transactions to hide criminal proceeds\n\n2. Common legal definitions include:\n- Intentionally obscuring the origins of criminal proceeds\n- Engaging in financial transactions to promote unlawful activity\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legal\n\n3. Typical statutory requirements:\n- Knowledge that funds derive from criminal activity\n- Purposeful attempt to conceal or disguise fund origins\n- Transporting, transferring, or transmitting funds with criminal intent\n\n4. Jurisdictional variations exist, but most definitions involve:\n- Deliberate financial manipulation\n- Criminal intent\n- Proceeds from specified unlawful activities\n\nThis overview provides general legal perspectives, but specific definitions can vary between jurisdictions and legal systems.",
